gize' employees' proactivity, especially in interdependent and uncertain work environments. In this pioneering work, expert scholars offer new thinking on the process by examining how emotion can drive employees' proactivity in the workplace and how, in turn, that proactivity can shape one's emotional experiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEmotions. 0aEmployee motivation. 0aPsychology, Industrial. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Organizational Behavior.2bisacsh1 aAshkanasy, Neal M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBindl, Uta K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCangiano, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Zhijun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChi, Nai-Wen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuang, Emily Guohua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJi, Shunhong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamran-Morley, Daniya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebel, R. David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Chenwei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Wanlu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiao, Zhenyu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Wu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadrid, Hector P., econ